# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Certainly! Here's the intuition behind my code in simpler terms:

1. The code counts the occurrences of rows and columns in a grid using two maps: `pq` for rows and `col` for columns.

2. It iterates over each row and increments its count in the `pq` map.

3. It extracts the values of each column and stores them in the `col` map, incrementing their count.

4. Then, it iterates over the rows and checks if the corresponding column exists in the `col` map.

5. If a matching column is found, it calculates the count of equal pairs by multiplying the counts of the row and column.

6. It adds this count to the total count of equal pairs.

7. Finally, it returns the total count of equal pairs.

The code efficiently counts the occurrences of rows and columns and determines the count of equal pairs by comparing the maps.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:$$O(n^2)$$

- Space complexity:$$O(n)$$

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int equalPairs(vector<vector<int>>& grid) {
        map<vector<int>,int> pq;  // Map to count occurrences of each row
        int n=grid.size();
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            pq[grid[i]]++;  // Count occurrences of each row
        }

        map<vector<int>,int> col;  // Map to count occurrences of each column
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            vector<int> temp;
            for(int j=0;j<n;j++)
            {
                temp.push_back(grid[j][i]);  // Extracting column values and storing them in a vector
            }

            col[temp]++;  // Count occurrences of each column
        }

        int count=0;
        for(auto &i:pq)
        {
            if(col.find(i.first)!=col.end())  // Check if the column exists in the map
            {
                count += (i.second)* col[i.first];  // Calculate the count of equal pairs
            }
        }
        return count;  // Return the count of equal pairs

    }
};

