# Intuition

# Approach
There are three approaches to solve this question
First is Brute force
We check each row with each column and if they are the same, we add one to the count
Second is also Brute force but reduces some comparisons
We store the sum of each row and column in another vector and only compare the row and column if there sums are equal
Third approach is using maps
Push all the row vectors into a map, 
Then increment the count by the frequency of how many times a column appears in the map
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
    O(n^2), as we go over the whole matrix
- Space complexity:
    O(n) 
###    
